        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(models): add Claude Sonnet 5 support",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nAnthropic now exposes Claude Sonnet 5 as `claude-sonnet-5`, but OpenClaw did not yet model its catalog metadata, thinking contract, request restrictions, provider routes, or CLI aliases. Users need to select Sonnet 5 without breaking existing explicit Sonnet 4.6 configurations.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\n- Add exact Sonnet 5 catalog metadata: 1M context, 128k output, current pricing/cache rates, image input, and adaptive thinking.\n- Route Sonnet 5 through native Anthropic, Claude CLI, Vertex, Cloudflare AI Gateway, and Amazon Bedrock Mantle while keeping unsupported legacy Bedrock paths excluded.\n- Enforce the model contract across SDK and native transports: adaptive-thinking defaults and opt-out behavior, sampling restrictions, refusal streaming, and unconditional assistant-prefill removal.\n- Advance the generic `sonnet` shorthand to Sonnet 5 without overwriting user-authored aliases or changing provider-specific defaults that intentionally remain on Sonnet 4.6.\n- Keep generated plugin SDK baselines, focused tests, provider docs, and transcript-hygiene docs aligned.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can select `anthropic/claude-sonnet-5` and supported provider equivalents, while existing explicit Sonnet 4.6 configurations remain available. Claude CLI `sonnet` now resolves to Sonnet 5, and explicit thinking-off requests use the supported provider-specific behavior. Unsupported legacy Bedrock routing remains unavailable instead of failing at runtime.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Official Anthropic model and migration contracts: https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview and https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/migration-guide\n- Final structured branch autoreview against `origin/main`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings, 0.96 confidence.\n- Final Blacksmith Testbox-through-Crabbox changed-files gate: `tbx_01kwe23e0smze9qbd6s1vg9han`, exit 0. This covered core/core-test/extension/extension-test typechecks, core and extension lint, import cycles, generated/package guards, and architecture guards.\n- Final live Azure Crabbox E2E: run `run_6541408af644`, lease `cbx_1c8a09786a33`, actual `Standard_D32ads_v6`; `openclaw infer model run --local --model anthropic/claude-sonnet-5` returned exactly `SONNET5_OPENCLAW_OK`, exit 0, lease cleanup confirmed.\n- Focused local proof: 19 model-default tests, 45 native Anthropic transport tests, and 30 Anthropic Vertex stream tests passed; formatting, scoped lint, and `git diff --check` passed.\n\n",
